title_as_recorded: Draft petition, 1652 [October?] 20, to the Parliament of England for support against incursion of other religious sects into the Massachusetts Bay Colony :
author_as_recorded: General Court of the Colony of Massachusetts
physical_description: Extent: 1 volume (2 leaves) : paper, 20 x 31 cm
note: The document was drafted by the Council of Magistrates under Edward Rawson. Corrections were made to the document by the Council of Deputies under William Torrey; these include the redaction of Anabaptists from the list of undesirable groups, originally listed as 'Manichies, Mahumetans, Jewes, Anabaptists, Familists, Adamites, Raunters, Levellers, papists, Athiests or what not'. Corrections were approved by the magistrates and the document was signed by John Endecott (1588?-1665), second Colonial Governor of Massachusetts. In 1785 the document was reused for note-taking and pen trials; names written on it include Hon. James Warren, Samuel Green, Elisha May, John Inglee, and others.
